                <p>
                    At the deepest level, computers don't "think"—they just open and close billions of tiny electronic
                    switches.
                    Boolean Logic is the mathematical system that governs these switches. In this topic, you will learn
                    how to
                    control the flow of 1s and 0s using Logic Gates, creating circuits that can make decisions, do
                    maths, and store data.
                </p>
