                <div style="margin-top: 1rem;">
                    <p>This topic covers the theoretical foundation of computer decision making:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Logic Gates:</strong> Identifying and defining the six standard gates: NOT, AND, OR,
                            NAND, NOR, and XOR.</li>
                        <li><strong>Logic Circuits:</strong> Combining gates to solve specific problems or represent
                            logic expressions.</li>
                        <li><strong>Truth Tables:</strong> Creating tables that map every possible input combination (1s
                            and 0s) to a final output.</li>
                        <li><strong>Logic Expressions:</strong> Writing mathematical statements (e.g., A AND B) to
                            represent circuits and problems.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
