                <div class="section-body">
                    <h4>What you need to know:</h4>

                    <div class="learning-points">
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Identification:</strong> Identify and use the standard symbols for logic gates.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Definition:</strong> Define and understand the functions of the standard logic
                                gates:
                                <ul>
                                    <li>NOT</li>
                                    <li>AND</li>
                                    <li>OR</li>
                                    <li>NAND</li>
                                    <li>NOR</li>
                                    <li>XOR (EOR)</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Nested Notes Collapsible -->
                    <details class="notes-box">
                        <summary>
                            <h4>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-lightbulb"></i> Notes & Guidance</span>
                                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down toggle-icon"></i>
                            </h4>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="notes-content">
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Inputs:</strong>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li><strong>NOT</strong> is a single input gate.</li>
                                        <li>All other gates (AND, OR, NAND, NOR, XOR) are limited to <strong>two
                                                inputs</strong> for this syllabus.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>XOR (Exclusive OR):</strong> Outputs 1 only if the inputs are
                                    <em>different</em> (one is 1, the other is 0). If both are 1, it outputs 0.
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>NAND/NOR:</strong> These are the "Not AND" and "Not OR" gates. They output
                                    the exact opposite of their standard counterparts.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                </div>
            </details>

