                        </summary>
                        <div class="notes-content">
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Complexity Limit:</strong> Logic circuits will be limited to a maximum of
                                    <strong>three inputs</strong> and <strong>one output</strong>.
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>Drawing Circuits:</strong> Circuits must be drawn clearly for the statement
                                    given, without simplification. Lines should join components directly.</li>
                                <li><strong>Expression Format:</strong> Use standard notation, e.g.,
                                    <code>(A AND B) OR (NOT C)</code>. Brackets are crucial to show which operations
                                    happen first.
                                </li>
