                    <h4>What you need to know:</h4>

                    <div class="learning-points">
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Completion:</strong> Complete a truth table from:
                                <ul>
                                    <li>A given problem statement.</li>
                                    <li>A logic expression.</li>
                                    <li>A logic circuit.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Binary Output:</strong> Produce the binary output from all the possible binary
                                inputs.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Nested Notes Collapsible -->
                    <details class="notes-box">
                        <summary>
                            <h4>
                                <span><i class="fa-solid fa-lightbulb"></i> Notes & Guidance</span>
                                <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down toggle-icon"></i>
                            </h4>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="notes-content">
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Rows:</strong> The number of rows in a truth table is $2^n$, where $n$ is
                                    the number of inputs.
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>2 Inputs = 4 Rows (00, 01, 10, 11).</li>
                                        <li>3 Inputs = 8 Rows (000 to 111).</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>Intermediate Columns:</strong> When solving complex circuits, it is helpful
                                    to add extra columns for the intermediate steps (e.g., the output of the first AND
                                    gate) before calculating the final output.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </details>
